properties.title: Homage
properties.description:
This mural is a tribute to John Carlos and Tommie Smith’s protest on Oct. 16, 1968 at the Olympics in Mexico City. United States track athletes and San José State University students Tommie Smith and John Carlos took a stand when they received their medals. They protested the unjust treatment of African American people in the United States. They took a stand against poverty and inequality. This mural was produced by Anno Domini and San José Downtown Association in 2005.

Image Source: Yan-Yin Choy.
Source: Lakey, Cherri. “Find Beauty in the Streets of San Jose This Summer.” KQED, KQED, 5 July 2016, http://www.kqed.org/arts/11741855/find-beauty-in-the-streets-of-san-jose-this-summer.

Paul J Gonzalez painted this mural, with design help from Monika Rose and painting in collaboration with Chris Carrillo. It was painted in March 2018. View a photo of the mural.

properties.title: Veggielution Farm Outdoor Kitchen Mural
properties.description:
MMAP painted this mural with NVIDIA volunteers at Veggielution, as part of NVIDIA's Project Inspire in 2012. MMAP artist Sarah Woodward and NVIDIA engineer Randy Reynolds collaborated to design the mural. Sarah Woodward, Scape Martinez, Laura Nagle and Yetunde Olagbaju completed the mural highlights. The mission was commissioned by NVIDIA. You can find this mural at Veggielution community farm's outdoor kitchen at Emma Prusch Park in San José. Read this blog to learn more.


Image Source: Yan-Yin Choy. Source: MMAP, http://www.muralmusicarts.org/blog/nvidia-2012/
